ixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add bay leaves, cardamom, cinnamon, saffron, paprika and chilli powder and cook <b>3 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add tomatoes, thyme, wine, salt, pepper, stock paste and water and cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Carefully transfer tomato mixture into casserole dish with rice and stir to combine. Cover with a lid or aluminium foil and bake for 20 minutes (180°C)."},{"content":"Remove casserole dish from oven, add reserved vegetables and stir to combine (be sure to scrape rice from edges of casserole dish), ensuring that vegetables are coated in rice mixture. Cover and stand for 15-20 minutes, fluffing rice every 5 minutes to ensure even absorption."},{"content":"Remove bay leaves, cinnamon quill and cardamom pods, if desired. Garnish with silvered almonds before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or<em> Everyday Cookbook <\/em>for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","This recipe is a source of zinc, calcium, iron and vitamin C."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","6 portions"]}